cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite both the repository and the paper."
title: "Asymmetric Loss Modulation Resolves the Voting Ensemble Paradox in Learned Context-Pruning Ensembles"
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: "Peter"
    family-names: "Lodri"
    orcid: "https://huggingface.co/PeetPedro"
    affiliation: "Independent, community-funded research"
repository-code: "https://github.com/peterlodri-sec/longrun-eval-kompress"
url: "https://pocoo.vaked.dev"
abstract: >-
  Multi-checkpoint voting ensembles with asymmetric training-data floors
  collapse to the per-stratum weakest voter under k-of-N drop voting. A 3.0x
  heavy false-eviction penalty on critical-syntactic tokens resolves this by
  lifting the collapse floor uniformly. We instantiate the method in
  kompress-v8, a 149M-parameter dual-head ModernBERT trained via C3
  self-distillation with a Qwen2.5-7B teacher. 17 models trained, 8 teachers,
  4 architectures, $38.95 total cost.
keywords:
  - context-pruning
  - voting-ensemble
  - loop-engineering
  - modernbert
  - token-compression
  - asymmetric-loss
  - self-distillation
